HEADWORD: Infundibulate
<hw>In`fun*dib"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Infundibulum</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the form of a funnel;
pertaining to an infundibulum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Infundibulate Bryozoa</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,<cd>a
group of marine Bryozoa having a circular arrangement of the tentacles
upon the disk.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infundibuliform</ent>⟦br⟧
